text: Litoria spartacus is a frog from Papua New Guinea. The male adult frog is 35.8 to 37.3 mm long from nose to rear end and the female is 51.1 mm long. The male has vocal slits. The frog has bright yellow colouring on its legs. This frog is yellow-green on the back and lighter on the belly. It has white marks under its eyes. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Litoria spartacus
